{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, the modern peer review process was born.",
    "Peer review has become a cornerstone of the academic prestige economy.",
    "Today, research that is disseminated outside of the peer review system receives little weight in most institutional evaluations.",
    "In many fields, commercial publishers dominate the landscape and thus control the academic prestige economy.",
    "In 2015, it was estimated that 70% of the articles in the social sciences and 50% of the articles in the natural sciences were published by one of four large commercial firms (Springer Nature, Elsevier, Wiley-Blackwell, and Taylor & Francis) (17)."
  ]
}